{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon","description":"## Why\nThe auto-lander is a long-running service; it must deploy like the review-bot and log to its OWN service logs — writing to `session_log` would blur that type's purpose (it is for agentic sessions, not CI/infra processes).\n## What\nContainerize the service and wire it into docker-compose (single instance) on the existing Gerrit box; route logs to container stdout → the existing CloudWatch monitoring.\n## Scope\nDeploy + observability + single-instance guard. Not the loop logic.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` + a compose service in `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`; single instance (serialized — a lock so two copies never run).\n- [ ] Credentials wired like the review-bot: RebarBotNava with `rebaseOnBehalfOfUploader` + submit permissions; secrets provisioned, not inlined.\n- [ ] Logs go to container stdout → existing CloudWatch monitoring (`infra/terraform/monitoring_*.tf`); the service NEVER writes `session_log`.\n- [ ] Health/liveness signal + restart policy; a stuck/hung wipChain is detectable (timeout → park + surface via the outcome contract).","id":"3c55-2af3-0c9c-4b11","parent_id":"f1fa-57d8-07cb-44af","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S5 Deploy (container + compose, single instance) + observability (service logs, not session_log)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783721691676505001,"uuid":"cce60c30-22f6-43fd-8b66-34eb1bff2206"}